    <description>Android Studio is the official  Android development environment based on IntelliJ IDEA. Similar to Eclipse with the ADT Plugin, Android Studio provides integrated Android developer tools for development and debugging. On top of the capabilities you expect from IntelliJ, Android Studio offers:

* Flexible Gradle-based build support.
* Build variants and multiple apk file generation
* Code templates to help you build common app features
* Rich layout editor with support for drag and drop theme editing
* Lint tools to catch performance, usability, version compatibility and other problems.
* ProGuard and app-signing capabilities.
* Built-in support for Google Cloud Platform, making it easy to integrate Google Cloud Messaging and App Engine
* And much more

      http://developer.android.com/tools/studio/index.html
    </description>
